    <section class="content" id="about">
        <h2>About Us</h2>
        <p>Mr. Pingvin is dedicated to developing students academically and morally to prepare them for a meaningful life.</p>
        <h3>Mission</h3>
        <p>To nurture the core values and promote appropriate behavior of every student at St. Jude Parish School.</p>
        <p>To develop a society where students show respect and integrity, guiding students to reflect on their actions.</p>
        <p>To foster a community that appreciates the practice of personal growth and development.</p>
        <p>To practice proper and respectful behavior not just within the school community but also in the wider community.</p>

        <h3>Vision</h3>
        <p>We envision a learning environment where every student values respect, kindness, and personal growth, applying these principles in their daily lives.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="content" id="values">
        <h2>What are Values?</h2>
        <p>Values are principles that guide actions and decisions, shaping individuals into responsible and empathetic members of society.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="content" id="how">
        <h2>How Can We Build Strong Values?</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Lead by example – Show honesty, kindness, and respect.</li>
            <li>Encourage reflection – Help students think about their actions.</li>
            <li>Promote responsibility – Assign tasks that teach accountability.</li>
            <li>Use real-life lessons – Apply values in everyday situations.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="content" id="reminders">
        <h2>Why Are Values Important?</h2>
        <p>Values shape our character and define how we interact with others. They help us make ethical decisions and contribute positively to society.</p>
    </section>

